==English==

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[auspicatus]]'', past participle of ''[[auspicari]]'' "to take [[auspices]]", from ''[[auspex]]'' "bird seer", "augur", a contraction of ''[[avispex]]''; ''[[avis]]'' "bird" + ''[[specere]]'', ''[[spicere]]'', "to view".

===Adjective===
'''auspicate'''
# [[auspicious|Auspicious]].

